name: Homecoming
overview: Heidi Bergman is a caseworker at Homecoming, a Geist Group facility helping soldiers transition to civilian life. Years later she has started a new life, living with her mother and working as a waitress, when a Department of Defense auditor questions why she left the Homecoming facility. Heidi quickly realizes that there's a whole other story behind the story she's been telling herself.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Jackie finds herself floating in a boat in the middle of a lake, with no memory of how she got there - or even who she is. Her search for her identity will lead her into the heart of the Geist Group.

episodes.name: Optics
episodes.overview: If a client experiences adverse effects to the treatment, domestic reassignment may be a better path to success.

episodes.name: Helping
episodes.overview: Life-skills activities allow the client to envision life after Homecoming, practicing social interactions in a safe and nurturing setting.

episodes.name: Toys
episodes.overview: Outside visitors, though well-intentioned, may disrupt the gradual transition back to civilian life.
